*ruby-gtkmozembed-0.19.0 (16 Jul 2009)

  16 Jul 2009; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org>
  +ruby-gtkmozembed-0.19.0.ebuild,
  +files/ruby-gtkmozembed-0.19.0-gtkmozembed.h-fix.patch:
  Version bump for ruby-gnome2 0.19.0. Drop seamonkey support since upstream
  does not support it anymore.

  09 Dec 2008; Ferris McCormick <fmccor@gentoo.org>
  ruby-gtkmozembed-0.16.0.ebuild:
  Sparc stable, Bug #215149.

  14 Oct 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org>
  ruby-gtkmozembed-0.16.0.ebuild:
  Add proper dependencies for xulrunner, firefox, and seamonkey. Fixes #239577.

  15 May 2008; Markus Meier <maekke@gentoo.org>
  ruby-gtkmozembed-0.16.0.ebuild:
  amd64 stable, bug #215149

  22 Apr 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org>
  -ruby-gtkmozembed-0.15.0.ebuild:
  Remove old version

  02 Apr 2008; Christian Faulhammer <opfer@gentoo.org>
  ruby-gtkmozembed-0.16.0.ebuild:
  stable x86, bug 215149

  29 Mar 2008; Brent Baude <ranger@gentoo.org>
  ruby-gtkmozembed-0.16.0.ebuild:
  Marking ruby-gtkmozembed-0.16.0 ~ppc for bug 215149

  29 Mar 2008; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org>
  +files/ruby-gtkmozembed-0.16.0-seamonkey.patch,
  ruby-gtkmozembed-0.16.0.ebuild:
  Fix seamonkey support for 0.16.0 with a new patch that takes into account that
  0.16.0 already has support for different gecko providers. Reported in #215149.

  28 Mar 2008; Ferris McCormick <fmccor@gentoo.org>
  ruby-gtkmozembed-0.16.0.ebuild:
  Add ~sparc for testing, related to Bug #215149.

  17 Jan 2008; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  ruby-gtkmozembed-0.16.0.ebuild:
  Add missing pkg-config dependency. Thanks Patrick in bug #206216.

